lead_paragraph: Louise Friberg of Sweden won her first L.P.G.A. Tour title in her fourth career start, closing with a seven-under-par 65 on Sunday for one-stroke victory over Yani Tseng of Taiwan in the MasterCard Classic in Huxquilucan, Mexico. Friberg, 10 strokes behind Ji-Young Oh at the start of play Sunday after opening rounds of 72 and 73, had an eagle, six birdies and a bogey.
